&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As far as what shaman want, I read the huge thread on the old Newbie Zone, as did others on the team and there were no conclusions.&amp;nbsp; I also read many of the threads on the Shamans Crucible.&amp;nbsp; What I saw was a lot of ,the grass is greener, and class envy.&amp;nbsp; One email, from a prominent shaman even stated, we don't know what we want, we just want something.&amp;nbsp; That's not much information to go on.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Even here in this thread, I see division among shaman players, where what some perceive to be broken, others think is just fine.&amp;nbsp; You ask for statements and communication, while it is hard to comment when the message you are receiving is not unified and for the record the "What's a shaman" comment was meant as a joke. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;As I stated when I started this position, I will listen, but that does not mean your ideas will be implemented. &amp;nbsp;It may be that nothing is changed with shaman in the near future but if you provide a comprehensive list of what exactly&amp;nbsp;shaman think does not work, I will pass it along.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
