    <item>
      <title>Re: sShaman Prayers Have Been Heard By the Developers!</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=13789#M13789</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I must admit--I'm a bit stunned.&amp;nbsp; I wasn't really expecting a response.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I've erased this response twice.&amp;nbsp; I don't want to start bitching again.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Brenlo, bottom line, the shaman recognize that we're a utility class.&amp;nbsp; We comprise a huge number of different play styles.&amp;nbsp; We made that open letter detailing problems within the shaman community, but I think it was a bit of a mistake.&amp;nbsp; It has two major problems.&amp;nbsp; First, as a summary argument, it lacks all the detailed statistical proof that we had spread out across various other threads.&amp;nbsp; That means that a casual reader who wanders over and reads it will be thinking, "My god, what a bunch of whiny bastiges!"&amp;nbsp; Second, since we recognized that shaman is&amp;nbsp;a utility class, we offered potential solutions to just about every deficit category.&amp;nbsp; Perhaps we didn't make the introduction clear enough or emphasized it enough.&amp;nbsp; ALL of those changes would be vastly overpowered and unbalancing.&amp;nbsp; None of us want an EQ god--what would be the point?&amp;nbsp; No challange, no fun.&amp;nbsp; We categorically stated that changes in one or two areas would make the other suggestions moot.&amp;nbsp; We (perhaps mistakenly) assumed that SoE had some vision for shaman and would (hopefully) select those suggestions that (a) were not overpowering (b) were in line with SoE's vision of the class, but (c) had some marginal utility effect.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As several of the other posters have noted, the vast majority of our frustration stems from a complete lack of communication.&amp;nbsp; There were some excellent suggestions in that thread.&amp;nbsp; Some very novel.&amp;nbsp; Some were, in my opinion, silly.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;One thing I requested in a number of feedbacks, emails, and posts (all of which were ignored), was that SOMEONE from SoE simply open up a line of communication with the shaman.&amp;nbsp; I honestly think the single best thing that can be done at the moment, especially since SoE doesn't appear to have any kind of vision for the shaman class, is to have a moderated chat of some kind.&amp;nbsp; As I noted, for maybe an hour or something, having a Customer Service Rep and a Developer in a live chat with the shaman is not a huge investment of time.&amp;nbsp; Not even all of the shaman--just a few representational shaman so you don't get spammed with tells.&amp;nbsp; I think the Crucible represents one of the largest, if not the largest, online shaman communties in the game.&amp;nbsp; If you honestly want to hear what we have to say, have an online chat with 3 or 4 of us from the Crucible.&amp;nbsp; We'll elect a couple of people to represent us and explain what's been going wrong.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Just please don't go radio silent on us for months again and leave us hanging in the wind.&amp;nbsp; I honestly was not kidding hearing from about 14 long-time high level shaman who've retired from this last expansion.&amp;nbsp; It's THAT bad for shaman right now.&amp;nbsp; We can't heal.&amp;nbsp; We can't provide half-way decent dps in short fights, and we can't really buff.&amp;nbsp; Our most effective use right now is to stand outside and focus groups going into trials.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Chutoi&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
