      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=13705#M13705</link>
      <description>Brenlo,&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It has been stated by SoE that you have people on the development team that play all classes.&lt;br&gt;Then you stated that there has been no consenus over what the Shaman need if anything.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ok well first what did those Shaman tell you?&lt;br&gt;Second what level of play at they at?&lt;br&gt;Have they done GoD trials?&lt;br&gt;What was their reaction to that?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our proposal was pretty clear and consise about what we could use.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I will try to simplify that into how I feel at this time.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I am a PRIEST class. First foremost this is what a Shaman is or at least WAS.&lt;br&gt;What do priests do? Well we heal mainly.&lt;br&gt;Whether some like that or not it is what the Shaman is and what the orignal design of us was.&lt;br&gt;Can a Shaman function as even a patch healer effectively in GoD? No.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;No class envy no comparisons to muddle things. Simply we can not fufil the role of a Priest class in GoD.&lt;br&gt;We do not have DPS for short fights. Every expansion fights have become shorter.&lt;br&gt;We have basically in GoD have become a one trick pony.&lt;br&gt;We slow. Problem is the further you progress the less slow benfits you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We offer almost nothing to a group past a certain point but useless slows and inadequate heals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Well you have two real solutions.&lt;br&gt;Increase Shaman's ability to heal.&lt;br&gt;Or completely remove slow immunity and remove mitagation from all but boss encounters.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Since the latter is not very likely to happen we have been requesting the former.&lt;br&gt;I think where you might get muddled is where we have offered suggestions on other areas we could stand improvements.&lt;br&gt;Areas that would give us more versitility and utility and thus making the needed healing changes less of an issue.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We don't all quite agree on how much of a healing change is needed or at what point it is needed.&lt;br&gt;We do agree it is needed though.&lt;br&gt;We have tried to offer suggestions but in the end we have to rely on you to fairly conduct game balance.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Talking to us is a good start.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Here is my opinion of what we need.&lt;br&gt;A heal over time that is a TRUE upgrade in GoD.&lt;br&gt;Breathe of Trusher is pretty much an insult for a heal with mobs quadding for 1000+&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Some form of group heal spell.&lt;br&gt;It doesn't have to be killer just something that we can use even once in awhile.&lt;br&gt;Could be a direct heal, heal over time, it could even have a long 30-60 recast and use a decent amount of mana.&lt;br&gt;Personally I would like to see group forms of our heal over time spells.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We need an upgraded fast heal.&lt;br&gt;Tnarg does not cut it at 1300 when a mob is likely doing 3000+ a round either unslowed or mitagating.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We need a better cheal.&lt;br&gt;Ours is level 58 and never upgraded.&lt;br&gt;Completely ineffective at level 65 in GoD.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Some will not agree with me on that. Maybe not all that is needed. It is however what I personally would like to see.&lt;br&gt;What I consider balance though is if there is going to be immune and mitagating mobs my healing needs to adequate enough for me to fuction as a healer under these conditions.&lt;br&gt;I don't have to be the "best" at that just ABLE to do it REASONABLY well if I HAVE to.&lt;br&gt;There you have it without a single class comparison.&lt;br&gt;I just want my abilities to balance with each other in current game content.&lt;br&gt;Which at this time they do not do.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Sorry if we have not been EXACT with what we want.&lt;br&gt;And sorry here for being a bit frustrated and insulting but you have a highly trained, highly paid (paid by us), developement and research staff.&lt;br&gt;We have informed you that there is a problem.&lt;br&gt;Offered our suggestions as best we can and in as reasonable a manner as we can.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are simply asking for a few things that should not be unreasonable.&lt;br&gt;1) You talk with us regarding the issue&lt;br&gt;2) You work with your research people to confirm or deny our results&lt;br&gt;3) Produce a fix based on the results of the above&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I will also add your humor has not been well appreciated.&lt;br&gt;Your witty comment of "What is a Shaman?" was pretty insulting even when you knew it was supposed to be humor.&lt;br&gt;There is also other nice little pokes at us which we have not found all that funny.&lt;br&gt;Shaman spell vendor in GoD (AS zone) named Hatem.&lt;br&gt;You see we are a bit frustrated and poking fun at our frustration just isnt that funny to us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We will ask of you in good faith to at least discuss the matter with us openly and help us come to an equitable solution.</description>
