      <title>Re: sShaman Prayers Have Been Heard By the Developers!</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=13703#M13703</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Thank you for at least responding, Brenlo.&amp;nbsp; I don't know that I appreciate the insults of using soul binders and the new tradeskill UI as examples of actively listening to the community.&amp;nbsp; I think we all have quite a bit hope of these things changing and even just simply responding in this thread shows you are heading in the right direction.&amp;nbsp; But in the long run you'll need to do more.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;While I'm sure the shaman spells in GoD were made with the best intentions they don't at all address shaman concerns.&amp;nbsp; A 2.1 minute dot that does roughly 25 dps on mobs that live for 30 seconds is worthless.&amp;nbsp; A 60 hp per tick upgrade to a spell that only healed 300 a tick to start with on trash mobs that hit for 1200+ did nothing for our healing ability.&amp;nbsp; Breath of Trushar is similar to what regrowth was when it was introduced and trash mobs hit for 80-100.&amp;nbsp; The new cannibalize spell is really a tremendous idea but making it our ancient in GoD seems to defy logic.&amp;nbsp; This is a much needed spell for every shaman where most classes get their slightly upgraded nukes as their ancient which is obviously less critical.&amp;nbsp; I think everyone, let alone shaman, can agree with the above.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;In order to stay a relevant class in the semi-high to high end game we need upgrades in our healing and dps departments.&amp;nbsp; We aren't requesting massive or even large upgrades here.&amp;nbsp; Breath of Trushar needs to be changed to 500 a tick in order to be considered a heal over time.&amp;nbsp; 350 mana seems fair as this still leaves shaman slightly behind clerics in heal per tick and slightly ahead in HoT effeciency.&amp;nbsp; While this would certainly be helpful we still need a fast heal that is capable of keeping a rampage tank or even the main tank alive for one mob if the cleric/druid goes down.&amp;nbsp; A 1750 heal for 525 mana would still leave us well behind druids and clerics but would at least slightly fill the ever growing gap.&amp;nbsp; Replace Plague of Deluda with an 1100 nuke that casts in 6 seconds for 375 mana.&amp;nbsp; This still leaves us the worst nuker of any casting class but again slightly fills the gap in dps.&amp;nbsp; Make the nuke our ancient and make the new cannibalize accessible to more shaman.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Some shaman might ask for more, some less but I think this is a good medium.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; These aren't huge upgrades.&amp;nbsp; Shaman would still be a distant 3rd in healing power and at the bottom of the dps chain.&amp;nbsp; I've heard concern that upgrades would possibly unbalance the lower end&amp;nbsp;game but GoD spells only drop in GoD and are no drop so they will really only benefit the higher end shaman who desperately need help.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
