    <item>
      <title>Re: sShaman Prayers Have Been Heard By the Developers!</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=13682#M13682</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;Brenlo, I am a tad embarrassed for you and by association SOE. In a page of logical discussion about the limitations affecting shaman atm in THE current game progression path (Gates of Discord) your only reply lashes out and touts the implementation of &lt;EM&gt;wonderful changes&lt;/EM&gt; that (1) either no one cares about, (2) have been asked about since game creation and finally added, albeit rather flawed, and (3) in no way, shape or form makes an attempt to discuss or answer the questions, comments raised in this thread. This from the SOE representative. I am not sure what you were attempting to "diffuse" by finally commenting, but your style and comments just exponentially raised the level of belief by shaman that SOE has (1) no clue about shaman class problems, (2) doesn't care what&amp;nbsp;shaman class problems are, and, (3) have no intention of taking the day-to-day experience and knowledge of their shaman player base into account in defining what those&amp;nbsp;problems are. Frankly, if all you have to say is indicated by your post to this thread, you should not post.&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The shaman players fully understand the difficulties in keeping a game progressing that provides challenging content for players. What we do not understand is why that progression has focused on limiting to the point of extinction a single class of the game. Clerics complained about only being able to heal and have been given tools that make them a viable dps class. Druids complained about groupability and have been given enhanced tools that allow them to fill the role of primary healer/strong secondary healer. Paladins complained about limitiations of their class and have become significant tanks, buffers and healers. The list goes on until we get to shaman.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The&amp;nbsp;core ability we bring to the show is offset by new game mechanics (slow mitigation) and an increased number of totally unslowable mob encounters. This doesn't even take into account the abysmal resist rates of slow on ALL mobs. Frankly that is fine and I don't know many shaman who are against the idea of encounter changes as long as (1) we still have a role to play and (2) that role is as effective in a group as anyone else. To be clear on this, shaman are not complaining about the changes to the game. Shaman are complaining because these changes nullify our class existance.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Our buffs are moot at this level as melee stats are either maxxed or close to maximum. Our heals are sub-par in relation to damage intake. Unslowable mobs take away our class defining role. Mitigating mobs severely marginalize our class defining ability&amp;nbsp;allowing shaman&amp;nbsp;to be&amp;nbsp;replaced by other classes that can handle the slowing while contributing more effective tools to the group. Our dps contribution is non-existant for all pratical purposes. Shaman have tons of high damage spells - on paper. None of those spells are reasonably contributive in the events/groups due to long cast times, marginal direct damage, length of time for full damage effect and aggro on the caster.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Here is an irony embedded in all the shaman arguments for improvements: while pointing out the current uselessness of our heal spells to keep up with incoming damage, every serious comment/recommendation has pointed out we do not want to supplant druids as the 2ndary healing class. Inherently, shaman understand the need by SOE to find valid roles for each class. Druids needed the upgrades they received to find a spot as a desired grouping class. We do not contest that. Shaman were glad to see it happen. That said, this ironic position may be confusing yall on the seriousness of our complaints. That we understand and welcome and, perhaps even, commend the changes other classes have received to help them and can view changes to our class that would negate those benefits to other classes ... it does not mean we are conceding anything. On the one hand we are pointing out the obvious: SOE changed other classes significantly to increase their effectiveness while, either through lack of change or minimalized token additions, reducing the effectiveness of shaman as a class and as a contribution to game progression. Lot of words there to point out that since PoP, excluding LDoN, shaman have been severely NERFED.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Given that the planners/developers at SOE are not idiots we get back to the unanswered questions that are frustrating shaman: what is the vision of the shaman by SOE? What changes can we expect to either the game or the class to give us a viable contributory role? That is all we want to know. If that answer is that shaman are being phased out by the developing content then fine, tell us that so we know. If that answer is these questions are being looked at in development meetings and a plan is being worked out then, fine, tell us that so we know. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;In short, Brenlo,&amp;nbsp;to make a single post and not even address the topic, but rather tell us the world is perfect because there are portals in PoK and a new tradeskill UI is an insult to us and, should be, an embarrassment to you.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;---------------------------&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;While I was writing the above you posted again, Brenlo. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If, as you have stated, you are following key shaman threads and have discussed these and come to the point of "no conclusions" then I have to ask what are you missing? Is your deciding factor a single email from "a prominent shaman"? The threads on this topic are numerous and many of them give statistical/comparitive analysis of the exact problems shaman are facing. Not seeing does not make it non-conclusive.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Shaman are not whining about the grass being greener or class envy. As posted above, shaman recognize roles each class plays. Considering shaman were a definite group role class for much of EQ we know, better than most, what that means. There is no desire to take anything away from classes that have been changed to finally have a group role. But, that those changes have resulted in our role being taken away from us is a major concern.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Making sure secondary forte does not cap at 200 is a fix to code that should of not existed in the first place and once fixed will not grant shaman any benefit. Promising to look into something that you previously promised to look into is not confidence building to shaman. It either means you lied about looking into it previously or that the question you raised previously has not been addressed which further convinces us that shaman are not just on the back burner ... we are completely off the stove!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Application is the benchmark you need to view regarding what is perceived&amp;nbsp;as broken and not broken. GoD being the topic this thread addresses means that GoD is the benchmark. Those shaman who are hitting 65 and completely happy soloing named in Crushbone saying their abilities are awesome are not even on the same topic as the point of this thread: GoD and shaman niche in the expanison. Those not in GoD facing these problems cannot have an opinion with any validity. It really is that simple.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Your claim that "What's a shaman?" was a joke really drives the point home. That question, "What's a shaman?" is THE question we are asking at this point in the game. As pointed out, (1) are we a buffer? No, buffs are marginal at the high end of game as most melee stats are maxxed out with gear. (2) are we a healer? No, a healer repairs damage at a higher rate than sustained - we can not do that. (3) are we THE slower? No, mitigation and unslowable mobs prevent shaman from being THE slower. For mitigating mobs other classes bring more utility to a group that realistically requires the group to prefer the other class to the shaman. (4) are we dps? No, our damage output vs length of fight is laughable. Cleric summoned pets outdamage shaman in an effort expended/results obtained scenario.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;No one expects complete implementaton of all our ideas. Shaman were a diverse class of numerous tools that could be played various ways to acheive the same end result. That utility has evaporated. Suggestions on what specifically needs to be changed varies based on how the individual played their shaman. But here is the key: each and every shaman in GoD, while not on the same page about what should change, are equally serious about changes being needed. There is universal agreement that shaman in GoD have no role that consistantly contributes or that cannot be&amp;nbsp;accomplished better by other classes&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;succeed&amp;nbsp;in GoD&amp;nbsp;trial events.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As for providing a comprehensive list .. HELLO!! How many more lists do you need? How comprehensive does it have to be? You have them or access to them if, as you said, you are visiting the crucible.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Brenlo, I highly suggest you take the time and effort to communicate frequently with the shaman community on the crucible. You will deal with apathy, frustration and anger initially, but that will be short lived once the community recognized you are actually interested in determining if/what problems exist. Shaman are faced with extinction as an effective contributory class in GoD. Key word here is contributory. We want our role in this expansion. We want to contribute. If you want the answers to the&amp;nbsp;problems, take the time to come to us and work with us on those problems. Posting ocassionally that PoK portal stones have balanced the game and shows the depth and scope of SOE's commitment to making major changes to the game is not convincing us.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
