    <item>
      <title>Re: sShaman Prayers Have Been Heard By the Developers!</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=13689#M13689</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Brenlo,&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Thank you for replying.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;You see divison amongst shaman players. This is certainly true. When shaman are spread across the gamut of all EQ has to offer we might appear to be fine. I mean. If I as a level 65 shaman with 378 aa's and bazzar level gear head to seblis. I am fine. More than fine actually. But if I head to GoD and the trials. Or Hard missions in LDON. Well.. That is a different story.&amp;nbsp; There shaman are not at all fine.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Shamans greatest strength all throughout EQ's history has been one thing. Over time. Heals over time. Damage mitagation over time (Through slows) And Damage to monsters over time. By way of dots. All of this has a common component. Duration of fights. A cleric can heal a standard fight with a big C heal and maybe a smaller heal if things go awry. They can mitagate a little by way of nukes and or stuns. If stuff goes wrong they can res. A druid can ensure singles pulled and speed up fights with superior nukes and a get out of death free card if something goes wrong by way of an evvac. The strength tho is in the heals of both classes. Shaman can keep up with heals if slows land off the bat, and the tank doesnt take too much damage or lose aggro.&amp;nbsp;But the strength is based not off the heals. But the slows. And Slows are resisted.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;In a nutshell. I feel that shaman need a couple of things. A better blast heal found in GoD. In the first set of trials. Or purchased or quested for. In content that shaman can resonably be able to attempt with the spells we have now. These numbers have been tossed around on the shamans crucible all over the place. But I would feel a fair asking would be a 1750 hp heal For 525 mana or so. And a 3 second cast time and 200 range. A upgrade to Tnarqs. But not even close to what a druid and cleric get due to the ability of a shaman to mitagate so much damage through slow.&amp;nbsp; The second is to allow shaman to get back into the healing over time role that we first had before clerics. Breath of trushar is a good idea not taken far enough. 475 hit points healed per tick, for 6 ticks base for 280 mana or so. 100 range. That would give shaman a good longer term heal that they can apply before we get into the Tnarqs chain. With those two things and yourself or others coming to talk with shaman. We would shut the heck up. While people would continue to grumble about the addition of a disease dot that takes 2.1 minutes to run it's full course. Or the making of our canna upgrade the aincent spell. they would be grumbles. Not people yelling and screaming. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;First and foremost shaman are supposed to be the healers of the less civilized races. Let us do our job properly, please&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;With the current playstyle and leanings that the game has developed into. The game has been sped up beyond our tools that SoE has given us to cope. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;When a monster is pulled into camp, shaman are expected to do what one major thing. Slow the monster. Every monster. As fast as aggro allows. Why is this? Because once slowed a monster is much less of a threat. It makes the monsters damage slow to a crawl. that Enables shaman to heal the much lesser output of damage with thier heals over time (Both regen and Torpor/Quesance line) And if we have spiked damage a quick blast heal by way of Tnarqs. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Against a fully slowed monster. shaman can keep up. Even in GoD. But in GoD. It is very very hard to do so. Because much of the time we get stuck in a tnarq chain. We get a resist on slow. and the tank is in Ahhhhh crap range. So we spam a Tnarqs. And it just doesnt do enough.So we spam another praying that we get a crit so we have time to try another slow. Once in that chain.&amp;nbsp;If we get lucky. The monster dies. Before the tank dies. If we are unlucky the tank dies. Despite shaman spamming thier best heal spell for the situation.&amp;nbsp; This risk is what hurts shaman. We don't want to be the reason 5 other people are not having fun.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Bring slow mitagation into the equation and shaman are just not good enough healers. for the new content. So people start looking for someone who can slow and offer more to the makeup in the group since we have limited group slots, they only make do if none of the other classes are around. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Do shaman have to be in every group? No. But if I am in a group I want to be able to contribute like I used to. By being effective.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
