    <item>
      <title>Re: sShaman Prayers Have Been Heard By the Developers!</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=13680#M13680</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Brenlo,&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Let me help you understand why there is so much confusion.The shaman class is a complex class, we have many tools we can use, we have many duties we can perform and we have many options.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;This results in the fact that some shamans like our solo power, some like to duo and some like to group or raid.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Our current situation is different for these 4 types of shaman.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Solo'ers and players who duo are fine, they have what they need and in fact a shaman is one of the better classes for this kind of playstyle.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The raiding shaman is also fine until you happen to be the third (or higher) shaman on a raid, we do not stack well in a raid and I think you know this. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;However the major frustration you see here, on the shaman boards and even in game is from the grouping situation at the high end level of the game.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The average casual shaman is ok (not fine but ok as he is somewhere in the middle of the pack of the various classes) but at the high end things change.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The high end shaman finds himself facing mobs that mitigate slow or who are even slow imune, this shaman groups with players who all have maxed stats, this shaman encounters high DPS mob that have low HP (a mob type that does not allow our main source of damage (DoT's)&amp;nbsp;to work to the full extend) and this shaman now encounters missions and tasks where we are no longer able to perform as a healer.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;What we asked was that someone from the live team freed up some time to look into this, THAT is why we stated that WE do not know what we want to change (as we believed it was better to state what we felt was wrong and leave the correction in the hands of the devs) and that is also why you will see people stating that THEY are doing fine.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Because they are doing fine, they just do not encounter the problems the high end shamans face (not yet I should say).&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If the live team needs our input we are more then willing to give this to them, if they want our opinion we are more then willing to tell them what we think and even if they want idea's we can provide them. However WE can not solve this, in the end the live team and the devs have to decide what they want to change.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;And&amp;nbsp;WHEN (as I hope you guys can at least free up some time to post at the crucible about what you want from us) you look into this feel free to come over, after all we do not cry this hard because we are against you (even when that seems hard at times when you ignore us or joke about us) but because we feel a lot for the little toons we use in this online world. Why else would I have invested so much time into a character that atm is no fun to play and would I ask for a change instead of just canceling my accounts (I have&amp;nbsp;5 and&amp;nbsp;on them I have most classes at level 65) and move to the next game.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Stygiana&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
